    "<b>This scatter plot shows the relationship between access to exercise opportunities and adult obesity rates across 3,053 U.S. counties. We can see that there is a negative relationship: as exercise access increases, obesity rates tend to decrease, as shown by the downward sloping trend line. However the scatter is much wider than Plot 1 so exercise access alone does not strongly predict obesity which introduces the potential of omitted variable bias. This is a motivating factor for our regression model below where we add controls to better model the independent effect of exercise access on obesity.</b>\n",
